      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Eviction\" isn't the right term; usually, the city issues correction notices demanding the unauthorized structure or encroachment be remediated. They often start with warnings, but repeated disregard leads to fines escalating until the land is either returned to its intended public or private boundary. In extreme cases where the city wishes to reclaim the space, they have powers to compel removal through court action. Basically, they enforce the established boundaries rather than unilaterally ushering a business off school property.",
